<subSubSection lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="74" pageId="5" pageNumber="72" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="5.[227,372,1775,1801]" box="[227,372,1775,1801]" pageId="5" pageNumber="72">
<heading bold="true" box="[227,372,1775,1801]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="5" pageNumber="72" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[227,372,1775,1801]" pageId="5" pageNumber="72">Description</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[226,1439,1823,2063]" pageId="5" pageNumber="72">
<typeStatus box="[227,336,1823,1849]" pageId="5" pageNumber="72">Holotype</typeStatus>
MB.C.30440.1 is a haematitic internal mould consisting of two fully chambered segments; however, some chambers between the two segments are missing (
<figureCitation box="[1031,1163,1858,1884]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="6.[227,270,1962,1988]" captionTargetBox="[315,1340,306,1915]" captionTargetId="figure-52@6.[307,1355,302,1926]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Fig. 4. Rineceras tenerum sp. nov. from Oued Temertasset (all Korn et al. 2002 Coll.). A. Holotype MB.C.30440.1 (larger segment). B. Holotype MB.C.30440.1 (smaller segment). C. Paratype MB.C.30441. Scale bar units =1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6885206" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6885206/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="72">Fig. 4A–B</figureCitation>
). The total diameter is about 
<quantity box="[299,384,1894,1920]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.9" pageId="5" pageNumber="72" unit="mm" value="49.0">49 mm</quantity>
. At this diameter, the whorl profile is rounded-triangular with a somewhat flattened venter and continuously rounded dorsum. There is no overlap upon the previous whorl (
<figureCitation box="[1168,1262,1929,1956]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="7.[227,270,1926,1952]" captionTargetBox="[227,1436,1486,1894]" captionTargetId="figure-359@7.[227,1436,1486,1894]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Fig. 5. Rineceras tenerum sp. nov., holotype MB.C.30440.1 (Korn et al. 2002 Coll.) from Oued Temertasset. A. Whorl profile of the larger segment. B. Suture line, at ww =19.7 mm, wh= 13.7 mm. C. Whorl profile of the smaller segment. D. Suture line, at dm =26.3 mm, ww =11.3 mm, wh=8.0 mm. Scale bar units =1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6885210" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6885210/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="72">Fig. 5A</figureCitation>
). On the flanks and the outer part of the venter, there are twelve spiral lines on each side. The suture line shows a low amplitude; there is a wide, shallow external lobe and a low, tightly rounded ventrolateral saddle. On the flanks and dorsum the suture line is almost straight (
<figureCitation box="[839,931,2036,2063]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="7.[227,270,1926,1952]" captionTargetBox="[227,1436,1486,1894]" captionTargetId="figure-359@7.[227,1436,1486,1894]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Fig. 5. Rineceras tenerum sp. nov., holotype MB.C.30440.1 (Korn et al. 2002 Coll.) from Oued Temertasset. A. Whorl profile of the larger segment. B. Suture line, at ww =19.7 mm, wh= 13.7 mm. C. Whorl profile of the smaller segment. D. Suture line, at dm =26.3 mm, ww =11.3 mm, wh=8.0 mm. Scale bar units =1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6885210" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6885210/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="72">Fig. 5B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption pageId="6" pageNumber="73" startId="6.[227,270,1962,1988]" targetBox="[315,1340,306,1915]" targetPageId="6">
<paragraph blockId="6.[227,1437,1962,2059]" pageId="6" pageNumber="73">
