<paragraph blockId="7.[226,1437,654,927]" pageId="7" pageNumber="74">
The segment of the younger stage (
<figureCitation box="[652,745,654,680]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="6.[227,270,1962,1988]" captionTargetBox="[315,1340,306,1915]" captionTargetId="figure-52@6.[307,1355,302,1926]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Fig. 4. Rineceras tenerum sp. nov. from Oued Temertasset (all Korn et al. 2002 Coll.). A. Holotype MB.C.30440.1 (larger segment). B. Holotype MB.C.30440.1 (smaller segment). C. Paratype MB.C.30441. Scale bar units =1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6885206" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6885206/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="74">Fig. 4B</figureCitation>
) shows the conch dimensions and proportions better. The conch is evolute at 
<quantity box="[461,542,690,716]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.8" pageId="7" pageNumber="74" unit="mm" value="28.0">28 mm</quantity>
diameter (uw/dm =0.48). The whorl profile is similar to the large segment, but the venter is slightly more flattened and the ventrolateral shoulder is more pronounced with a very shallow submarginal ventral groove (
<figureCitation box="[662,755,760,787]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="7.[227,270,1926,1952]" captionTargetBox="[227,1436,1486,1894]" captionTargetId="figure-359@7.[227,1436,1486,1894]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Fig. 5. Rineceras tenerum sp. nov., holotype MB.C.30440.1 (Korn et al. 2002 Coll.) from Oued Temertasset. A. Whorl profile of the larger segment. B. Suture line, at ww =19.7 mm, wh= 13.7 mm. C. Whorl profile of the smaller segment. D. Suture line, at dm =26.3 mm, ww =11.3 mm, wh=8.0 mm. Scale bar units =1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6885210" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6885210/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="74">Fig. 5C</figureCitation>
). From the margin of the venter and on the flank, there are about 12 spiral lines. However, it can be seen that the number of spiral lines decreases during ontogeny; over a distance of 180 degrees, the initially coarse spiral lines in the submarginal area of the venter become weaker gradually. The siphuncle has a position slightly off centre on the ventral side. The suture line shows a broad and shallow external lobe and a very shallow lateral lobe (
<figureCitation box="[1136,1230,900,927]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="7.[227,270,1926,1952]" captionTargetBox="[227,1436,1486,1894]" captionTargetId="figure-359@7.[227,1436,1486,1894]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Fig. 5. Rineceras tenerum sp. nov., holotype MB.C.30440.1 (Korn et al. 2002 Coll.) from Oued Temertasset. A. Whorl profile of the larger segment. B. Suture line, at ww =19.7 mm, wh= 13.7 mm. C. Whorl profile of the smaller segment. D. Suture line, at dm =26.3 mm, ww =11.3 mm, wh=8.0 mm. Scale bar units =1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6885210" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6885210/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="74">Fig. 5D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[227,1436,966,1098]" pageId="7" pageNumber="74">
<typeStatus box="[227,330,967,993]" pageId="7" pageNumber="74">Paratype</typeStatus>
MB.C.30441 closely resembles the 
<typeStatus box="[756,859,966,992]" pageId="7" pageNumber="74">holotype</typeStatus>
but has a slightly more pronounced ventrolateral shoulder (
<figureCitation box="[344,437,1001,1027]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="6.[227,270,1962,1988]" captionTargetBox="[315,1340,306,1915]" captionTargetId="figure-52@6.[307,1355,302,1926]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Fig. 4. Rineceras tenerum sp. nov. from Oued Temertasset (all Korn et al. 2002 Coll.). A. Holotype MB.C.30440.1 (larger segment). B. Holotype MB.C.30440.1 (smaller segment). C. Paratype MB.C.30441. Scale bar units =1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6885206" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6885206/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="74">Fig. 4C</figureCitation>
). The large unfigured 
<typeStatus box="[693,794,1002,1028]" pageId="7" pageNumber="74">paratype</typeStatus>
MB.C.30442 has, at a whorl height of 
<quantity box="[1251,1337,1001,1028]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.1" pageId="7" pageNumber="74" unit="mm" value="21.0">21 mm</quantity>
, a whorl profile almost identical to the 
<typeStatus box="[577,683,1036,1062]" pageId="7" pageNumber="74">holotype</typeStatus>
; it also possesses twelve coarse spiral lines on the flanks and the outer part of the venter.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="74" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="7.[227,341,1137,1163]" box="[227,341,1137,1163]" pageId="7" pageNumber="74">
<heading bold="true" box="[227,341,1137,1163]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="7" pageNumber="74" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[227,341,1137,1163]" pageId="7" pageNumber="74">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[227,1438,1184,1316]" pageId="7" pageNumber="74">
The species of the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hyatt" authorityYear="1893" box="[532,649,1184,1209]" class="Cephalopoda" family="Trigonoceratidae" genus="Rineceras" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Nautilida" pageId="7" pageNumber="74" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[532,649,1184,1209]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="74">Rineceras</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be divided into different groups according to various aspects: general conch shape (whorls detached or embracing), whorl profile (depressed oval, rounded-triangular or trapezoidal), formation of the ventrolateral shoulder (rounded or angular), spiral ornament (spirals equally strong or differently strong) etc.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[227,1436,1355,1451]" pageId="7" pageNumber="74">
<taxonomicName authority="Korn &amp; Bockwinkel, 2022" authorityName="Korn &amp; Bockwinkel" authorityYear="2022" box="[227,451,1355,1380]" class="Cephalopoda" family="Trigonoceratidae" genus="Rineceras" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Nautilida" pageId="7" pageNumber="74" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="tenerum" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[227,451,1355,1380]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="74">Rineceras tenerum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[462,556,1355,1381]" pageId="7" pageNumber="74" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
differs from all other species of the genus by the combination of rather weak spiral lines that are restricted to the flank, the non-embracing whorls, and the whorl profile with a rounded-triangular outline.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
